DNS Server:  

Required files - place them in the same directory on the cs5700cdnproject.ccs.neu.edu machine:    
1. dnsserver.cpp
2. dnsserver.h
3. main.cpp
4. ip_lookup.py
5. Makefile

For the final submission, I've added a functionality of mapping based on geolocation.  
I've used the website https://geo.ipify.org/ and get the longitude and the latitude.
ip_lookup uses the api to lookup the geolocation and saves them to a file which dnsserver.cpp reads  
and performs the required calculations.  
I use the https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/haversine-formula-to-find-distance-between-two-points-on-a-sphere/  
geeksforgeeks website as a reference for doing the math. My code maps client to the closest ec2 node based  
on this distance.  
  
References:  
1. https://www.binarytides.com/dns-query-code-in-c-with-linux-sockets/  
2. https://beej.us/guide/bgnet/html/#datagram   
3. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ViTAg8YGI5Q   
4. https://geo.ipify.org/   
5. https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/haversine-formula-to-find-distance-between-two-points-on-a-sphere/  
  
How to run the server:  
$ make dnsserver
$ ./dnsserver -p port -n name  
Example:  
$ ./dnsserver -p 40006 -n cs5700cdn.example.com
How to test:  
$ dig cs5700cdn.example.com @cs5700cndproject.ccs.neu.edu -p 40006  
