HTTP Server:  
This http server uses simple LFU (least frequently used) algorithm for caching.  

Required files - place them in the same directory:
1. httpserver.py
2. httpserver
3. Makefile
4. deployCDN
5. runCDN
6. stopCDN
  
References:  
1. https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1392413/calculating-a-directorys-size-using-python  
2. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hFNZ6kdBgO0  
3. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DIPZoZheMTo&t=308s  
4. http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~cao/papers/zipf-implication/node7.html  

I tested it out using wget -O output.html http://ec2-54-213-74-38.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com:40006/w/index.php?title=Albert_Alcibiades_Margrave_of_Brandenburg-Kulmbach
from the cs5700cdnproject.ccs.neu.edu.
  
How to run:  
$ make httpserver  
$ ./httpserver -p port -o origin  
Example:  
$ ./httpserver -p 40006 -o ec2-54-158-114-217.compute-1.amazonaws.com  
  
How to run deploy|start|stopCDN:  
$ make CDN  
$ ./deployCDN -p 40006 -o ec2-54-158-114-217.compute-1.amazonaws.com -n cs5700cdn.example.com -u team-6 -i team-6.pem  
$ ./runCDN -p 40006 -o ec2-54-158-114-217.compute-1.amazonaws.com -n cs5700cdn.example.com -u team-6 -i team-6.pem  
$ ./stopCDN -p 40006 -o ec2-54-158-114-217.compute-1.amazonaws.com -n cs5700cdn.example.com -u team-6 -i team-6.pem  
  